Usage: sh makepBAM.sh <bam> <gref> <tref> <gtf>

input: <bam>, name of the bam file
<gref>, reference genome (path included)
<tref>, reference transcriptome (path included)
<gtf>, gtf file (path included)

output: <bam>.p.bam, a p.bam file with the same name as the <bam> file before the .bam extension

